WES MOORE, Governor Ch. 337
Chapter 337
(Senate Bill 161)
AN ACT concerning
Natural Resources – State Park Entry Fee – Exemptions
FOR the purpose of altering the individuals and vehicles that may enter a State park
without paying a certain fee on presentation of an accepted entrance document; and
generally relating to exemptions from paying State park entry fees.
BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
Article – Natural Resources
Section 5–1015
Annotated Code of Maryland
(2023 Replacement Volume and 2025 Supplement)
SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
Article – Natural Resources
5–1015.
(a) IN THIS SECTION, “ACCEPTED ENTRANCE DOCUMENT” MEANS A VALID
VETERAN IDENTIFICATION CARD, A DRIVER’S LICENSE OR OTHER STATE–ISSUED
LICENSE OR IDENTIFICATION CARD THAT INDICATES THE HOLDER IS A VETERAN, OR
ANY OTHER FORM OF IDENTIFICATION ACCEPTED BY THE DEPARTMENT THAT
ESTABLISHES THE HOLDER’S:
(1) VETERAN STATUS; OR
(2) FORMER MARYLAND NATIONAL GUARD STATUS IF THE HOLDER
WAS DISCHARGED OR RELEASED UNDER CONDITIONS OTHER THAN DISHONORABLE.
(B) On presentation of [a valid veteran identification card, a driver’s license that
indicates the license holder is a veteran, or any other form of identification accepted by the
Department that establishes the holder’s veteran status] AN ACCEPTED ENTRANCE
DOCUMENT BY AN INDIVIDUAL:
(1) [A veteran] THE INDIVIDUAL may enter a State park without paying
any day–use entry fee that has been established; and
– 1 –

Ch. 337 2026 LAWS OF MARYLAND
(2) A vehicle of which [a veteran] THE INDIVIDUAL is an occupant may
enter a State park without paying any per–vehicle fee that has been established.
[(b)] (C) This section does not exempt [a veteran or other] AN individual from
paying any other facility use services fees not described in subsection [(a)] (B) of this
section.
SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
October 1, 2026.
Approved by the Governor, April 28, 2026.
